    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Import your `custom.py` into your project.\r\n\r\n2. In `custom.py`, write the `move_to_south(this_painter)` function. While the `Painter` `can_move(\"east\")`:\r\n\r\n   * Move forward one space\r\n   \r\n   * If the `Painter` `can_move(\"south\")`, call your `turn_right(this_painter)` function\r\n\r\n3. Write the `move_to_east(this_painter)` function. While the `Painter` `can_move(\"north\")`:\r\n\r\n   * If the `Painter` `can_move(\"east\")`, call your `turn_right(this_painter)` function\r\n   \r\n   * Move forward one space\r\n\r\n4. Save `custom.py` to your Backpack.\r\n\r\n5. In `main.py`, import your functions.\r\n\r\n6. Use your functions to navigate to the traffic cone.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/01c071bc608201dfdc999466bd4bb2b8-u1l9-l4b.gif)",
